value:
The Kingdom of Askr...so full of
people and their noise. This is
not where I belong.

Everything here is so open.
There is too much space, too
much...light. Too much.$k$pI need to go to a dark space to put
myself at ease.

Elm is my faithful servant. He will
never shrink from a task I've given
him. Never.

We are all alone. No matter what you
do, no one will ever truly know you—
and you will not know them.$k$pThe only choice is to close everyone
and everything out.

I am no Askr. I have nothing to say
to you—or anyone.

I am Embla... Despite knowing my
disdain for other worlds, you have
chosen to bring me here... I see.
Face the endless dark.

However much power I am able
to gain, I will never again grant
it for the benefit of mortals.
Hmph...

...Tribute? Hm. I will not turn it away,
but expect nothing in return.

I am Embla. Summoned...here?
By this mortal? Infuriating.

I detest mortals. They are weak,
their lives too short to have any
real meaning.$k$pAnd their praises and oaths have
even less meaning.$k$pIt was Askr's curiosity that led me
to grant a mortal the power of my
blood when I did. How was I repaid?$k$pMortals showered me with gratitude.
They called me savior...a benevolent
god come to aid them.$k$pThey...devoted themselves to me.$k$pBut those memories are just that—
they remain ever in the past.$k$pHad it never happened, it would have
been for the better.
Emptiness enclose you!
Your future is undone.
Feel sorrow!
Suffer as I have.
Do not leave me...
Ahh... This seething envy...
...Sheer impudence.
The mortals chose Askr. All of them. Over me...
Elm is a faithful servant. He would never betray me...
Even alone in the absolute, I do not yearn for companionship... I do not know loneliness!
Mortals once loved me as they do Askr… I had no choice.
Though the words stick in my throat, I am with you—for now.
That will do.
No egress.
Darkness approaches.
